# Cloudflare Pages security headers (applied to every response).
#
# Clickjacking is the headline risk for a wallet dApp — a framed "Sign" button
# becomes a drainer trigger — so framing is denied two ways (modern + legacy).
# NOTE: a full script-src/connect-src CSP is intentionally NOT set here yet: it
# must be tuned and tested against the live wallet/RPC/WalletConnect flow when the
# full app deploys (a too-strict CSP silently breaks wallet connect). `frame-
# ancestors` only governs framing, so it is safe to ship now.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin-allow-popups
  X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off

# Long-cache the fingerprinted build assets (immutable).
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
